      <akn:section eId="sec_16_306">
        <akn:num>16-306</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Notice of adoption proceedings.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-306_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except as provided by subsection (b) of this section, due notice of pending adoption proceedings shall be given to each person whose consent is necessary thereto, immediately upon the filing of a petition. The notice shall be given by summons, by registered letter sent to the addressee only, or otherwise as ordered by the court.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-306_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A party who formally gives his consent to the proposed adoption, as provided by this chapter, thereby waives the requirement of notice to him pursuant to this section.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
